21/07/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Sunday (20 July) that the United States has asked Turkey to send peacekeeping forces to Iraq. In a television interview, Erdogan described the invitation as a sign of the successful partnership between Ankara and Washington. The local newspaper <I>Radikal </I> reports that 1,000 to 1,500 Turkish soldiers would be deployed initially. (Radikal, Hurriyet - 21/07/03; Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, AFP - 20/07/03)
